161
00:19:00,624 --> 00:19:03,710
Done. You can go.

162
00:19:06,295 --> 00:19:08,297
Now...

163
00:19:16,138 --> 00:19:18,724
Mr Lehnsherr.
I'd like to have one final talk

164
00:19:18,808 --> 00:19:24,522
about the house that Xavier built
and the machine called Cerebro.

165
00:19:33,113 --> 00:19:36,449
continue smoking that in here
and you'll spend the rest of your days

166
00:19:36,533 --> 00:19:42,747
under the belief that you're a six-year-old girl.

167
00:19:42,831 --> 00:19:46,960
- Can you do that?
- I'd have Jean braid your hair.

168
00:19:47,043 --> 00:19:49,212
Welcome back.

169
00:20:08,480 --> 00:20:12,693
- You want me to leave?
- No. Just don't move.

170
00:20:19,199 --> 00:20:24,038
These lights represent
every living person on the planet.

171
00:20:26,247 --> 00:20:28,916
The white lights are humans.

172
00:20:31,377 --> 00:20:33,796
And these are the mutants.

173
00:20:36,174 --> 00:20:41,262
Through Cerebro I'm connected to them,
and they to me.

174
00:20:43,973 --> 00:20:46,476
You see, Logan?

175
00:20:46,559 --> 00:20:49,062
We're not as alone as you think.

176
00:20:51,230 --> 00:20:56,485
I found the base at Alkali Lake.
There was nothing there.

177
00:20:56,568 --> 00:21:01,490
The broken line represents the path
of the mutant who attacked the president.

178
00:21:01,573 --> 00:21:05,202
I've been finding it difficult to get a lock on it.

179
00:21:05,994 --> 00:21:08,663
Well, can't you just concentrate harder?

180
00:21:08,747 --> 00:21:11,291
If I wanted to kill him, yes.

181
00:21:13,585 --> 00:21:15,879
There.

182
00:21:15,962 --> 00:21:19,298
Looks like he's finally stopped running.

183
00:21:34,063 --> 00:21:37,066
I need you to read my mind again.

184
00:21:46,700 --> 00:21:50,537
- I'm afraid the results will be the same as before.
- We had a deal.

185
00:21:50,620 --> 00:21:56,292
The mind is not a box can be simply unlocked
and opened. It's a beehive with a million...

186
00:21:56,376 --> 00:21:58,211
Spare me the lectures.

187
00:21:58,294 --> 00:22:05,802
I have no doubt that your amnesia, your adamantium
skeleton, the claws are all somehow connected, but...

188
00:22:05,885 --> 00:22:11,516
Logan, sometimes the mind
needs to discover things for itself.

189
00:22:12,224 --> 00:22:14,643
I promise you we'll talk again when I return.

190
00:22:14,727 --> 00:22:19,440
Oh, if you would be kind enough
to watch over the children tonight.

191
00:22:19,523 --> 00:22:22,985
Scott and I are going to visit an old friend.

192
00:22:36,165 --> 00:22:39,917
I'm sending the coordinates
of where the mutant's settled.

193
00:22:40,001 --> 00:22:42,962
As soon as you find him,
bring him back to the mansion.

194
00:22:43,046 --> 00:22:47,508
- Let's hope he cooperates.
- Yes, for his sake. Good luck.

195
00:23:54,573 --> 00:23:57,034
Stryker, William.

196
00:23:57,118 --> 00:23:59,244


